---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is UP a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)"
  description="UP is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. An adverb/preposition meaning toward a higher position. Extensions: UPS, CUP, PUP, SUP."
  keywords="is up a scrabble word, up scrabble, up valid scrabble, up points scrabble, two letter words scrabble, up extensions scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is UP a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)",
    "description": "UP is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS scoring 4 points. An adverb/preposition meaning toward a higher position.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-up-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is UP a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, UP is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS scoring 4 points (U=1, P=3). It functions as adverb, preposition, adjective, and verb." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words can UP extend into?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "UP extends to UPS, CUP, PUP, SUP, DUP, TUP, YUP. Many form 4+ letter words: CUPS, PUPS, UPON, UPDATE." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why is UP a good Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "UP scores 4 points from 2 tiles thanks to P=3. CUP and PUP extensions add C=3 or P=3 for 7 points. Plus UP hooks into compound words like UPON, UPDATE, UPSET." } }
    ]
  })} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is UP a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>3 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, UP is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. UP functions as an adverb, preposition, adjective, and verb — one of the most grammatically versatile 2-letter words. With P=3 providing solid base value, UP delivers above-average scoring for its length and creates compound word opportunities.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid Both</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">UP</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">4 points · U=1, P=3 · An adverb/preposition meaning toward a higher position</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">UP scores above average thanks to P=3. It hooks into CUP, PUP, SUP, and extends into compound words like UPON, UPDATE, UPSET, UPBEAT — giving strategic flexibility throughout the game.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">4 U-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">2 P-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">UP Extensions</h2>
      <p>UP hooks beautifully — front-hooks create 3-letter words, back-hooks form compounds:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">UPS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CUP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PUP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SUP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DUP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">YUP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy with UP</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">YUP is the best hook:</span> YUP scores 8 points (Y=4, U=1, P=3) from just 3 tiles. If you draw Y with UP on the board, front-hooking to YUP is almost always worth it.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CUP and PUP for P doubling:</span> Both score 7 points. PUP uses two P tiles turning surplus P into profit. CUP adds C=3 for reliable scoring.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">UP on premium squares:</span> P=3 on a DLS becomes P=6, making UP worth 7. On a DWS, UP doubles to 8. Place P on multipliers for maximum impact.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">UP is unique because it forms <span class="text-white font-medium">compound words as a prefix</span>: UPON, UPSET, UPDATE, UPBEAT, UPHOLD, UPTURN. This means UP on the board creates hook opportunities most 2-letter words can't match.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-up/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix UP in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-op-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OP a Scrabble Word? Yes!</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
